#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.58"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.58:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.58:0.2"
msgid "6. Sacittavagga"
msgstr "6. Your Own Mind"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.58:0.3"
msgid "58. Mūlakasutta"
msgstr "58. Rooted"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.58:1.1"
msgid "“Sace, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow other paths were to ask:"

msgctxt "an10.58:1.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃmūlakā, āvuso, sabbe dhammā, kiṃsambhavā sabbe dhammā, kiṃsamudayā sabbe "
"dhammā, kiṃsamosaraṇā sabbe dhammā, kiṃpamukhā sabbe dhammā, kiṃadhipateyyā "
"sabbe dhammā, kiṃuttarā sabbe dhammā, kiṃsārā sabbe dhammā, kiṃogadhā sabbe "
"dhammā, kiṃpariyosānā sabbe dhammā’ti, evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ "
"aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ kinti byākareyyāthā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, all things have what as their root? What produces them? What is "
"their origin? What is their meeting place? What is their chief? What is "
"their ruler? What is their overseer? What is their core? What is their "
"culmination? What is their final end?’ How would you answer them?”"

msgctxt "an10.58:1.3"
msgid ""
"“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā bhagavaṃnettikā bhagavaṃpaṭisaraṇā. Sādhu "
"vata, bhante, bhagavantaṃyeva paṭibhātu etassa bhāsitassa attho. Bhagavato "
"sutvā bhikkhū dhāressantī”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. He is our guide and our refuge. "
"Sir, may the Buddha himself please clarify the meaning of this. The "
"mendicants will listen and remember it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.58:2.1"
msgid "“Tena hi, bhikkhave, suṇātha, sādhukaṃ manasi karotha, bhāsissāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, mendicants, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.”"

msgctxt "an10.58:2.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an10.58:2.3"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.107"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.58:3.1"
msgid "“Sace, bhikkhave, aññatitthiyā paribbājakā evaṃ puccheyyuṃ:"
msgstr "“Mendicants, if wanderers who follow other paths were to ask:"

msgctxt "an10.58:3.2"
msgid ""
"‘kiṃmūlakā, āvuso, sabbe dhammā, kiṃsambhavā sabbe dhammā, kiṃsamudayā sabbe "
"dhammā, kiṃsamosaraṇā sabbe dhammā, kiṃpamukhā sabbe dhammā, kiṃ adhipateyyā "
"sabbe dhammā, kiṃuttarā sabbe dhammā, kiṃsārā sabbe dhammā, kiṃogadhā sabbe "
"dhammā, kiṃpariyosānā sabbe dhammā’ti, "
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, all things have what as their root? What produces them? What is "
"their origin? What is their meeting place? What is their chief? What is "
"their ruler? What is their overseer? What is their core? What is their "
"culmination? What is their final end?’ "

msgctxt "an10.58:3.3"
msgid ""
"evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ "
"byākareyyātha:"
msgstr "You should answer them:"

msgctxt "an10.58:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘chandamūlakā, āvuso, sabbe dhammā, manasikārasambhavā sabbe dhammā, "
"phassasamudayā sabbe dhammā, vedanāsamosaraṇā sabbe dhammā, samādhippamukhā "
"sabbe dhammā, satādhipateyyā sabbe dhammā, paññuttarā sabbe dhammā, "
"vimuttisārā sabbe dhammā, amatogadhā sabbe dhammā, nibbānapariyosānā sabbe "
"dhammā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Reverends, all things are rooted in desire. Attention produces them. "
"Contact is their origin. Feeling is their meeting place. Immersion is their "
"chief. Mindfulness is their ruler. Wisdom is their overseer. Freedom is "
"their core. They culminate in the deathless. And extinguishment is their "
"final end.’"

msgctxt "an10.58:3.5"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ puṭṭhā tumhe, bhikkhave, tesaṃ aññatitthiyānaṃ paribbājakānaṃ evaṃ "
"byākareyyāthā”ti."
msgstr ""
"When questioned by wanderers who follow other paths, that’s how you should "
"answer them.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.58:3.6"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
